oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Fire Department from Jackson, Tennessee
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of members of the Jackson Fire Department, with their fire equipment assembled on a street in front of O. J. Nance Company Drugs. There is one firetruck and some horse drawn fire equipment as well as a dog on the street.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Drugstores; Stores & shops; Dogs; Horses; Automobiles; Fire fighters; Hose carriages; Firefighting equipment
